Package: cl-araneida-%type_pkg[lisp]
Version: 0.85
Revision: 1
Description: Webserver written in Common Lisp
License: BSD
Maintainer: Lars Rosengreen <lars@margay.org>

Type: lisp (sbcl)

Depends: fink-lisp-manager, %type_pkg[lisp], cl-net-telent-date-%type_pkg[lisp], cl-split-sequence-%type_pkg[lisp]

Source: http://ftp.linux.org.uk/pub/lisp/cclan/araneida_%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 456554ca92a78b07f748066b4d641479

SourceDirectory: araneida_%v

CompileScript: echo "nothing to do"

InstallScript: <<
  find %b -type d -name CVS -depth -exec rm -rf {} \;
  find %b -type f -name .cvsignore -exec rm -f {} \;
  %p/lib/common-lisp/scripts/install %type_pkg[lisp] araneida %i
<<

DocFiles: doc/* LICENCE LICENCE-diff NEWS Notes README TODO

PreRmScript: %p/lib/common-lisp/scripts/clean %type_pkg[lisp] araneida
PostInstScript: %p/lib/common-lisp/scripts/compile %type_pkg[lisp] araneida

DescDetail: <<
Araneida is a small extensible CL-based web server, designed to sit
behind a proxying Apache but also capable of being run standalone.
<<

DescUsage: <<
Stilll a little rough around the edges :)

%p --> where your fink installation is located (ie /sw)
%type_pkg[lisp] --> lisp implementation you are using (ie openmcl)

(require :asdf)
(pushnew #P"%p/lib/common-lisp/%type_pkg[lisp]/systems/" 
         asdf:*central-registry*)
(asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op 'araneida)
<<

